 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enraged Golem</span><hr size=1> He's a static spawn.. Pops under a belltower.<br><br>We did him with 22 people, a lvl 58 ranger co tanking with a 54 war.. only two clerics, and 2-3 druids, golem was unslowed.<br><br>I didnt try normal spells on him, just fire lures <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Mana wasn't going to hold out much anyways.. It's a terribly long fight, but pretty easy.<br><br><br>Edit :  3 days seems right, btw<br> <p>-Fallen/Rec- 58th Evoker < Aquilo Phoenix > <BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufallendeitydecandidus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FallenDeity Decandidus</A> at: 10/1/01 10:54:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukohpry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kohpry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 12:13:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~copperhawk/Ranger.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enraged Golem</span><hr size=1> A note on the agro sharing, since I was the ranger in question for Reclamation's fight:<br><br>The 54 warrior and I were in the same group.  Both the 54 warrior and I taunted, to keep the golem off of everyone else.  I'd tank it until my hit points dropped to 2 bubbles, then stop attacking and taunting and inch slowly backwards from the golem until it lost interest in me and turned on the warrior.  I'd wait a few seconds to let the warrior build agro, then start attacking again without taunting.  While the golem's attention was on the warrior, the main enchanter would drop a rune on me.  Once the warrior's health got to 2 bubbles, I'd resume taunting and grab agro back from the warrior. The enchanter would then rune the warrior and the cycle started over again.<br><br>Amazingly, we didn't lose anyone during that fight, though we were prepared to do combat rezzes.  I don't know all the details from their end of things, but there was a lot of good communication and coordination between the heal team members.  If you're going to try doing this without a higher level warrior, I'd suggest you have the healers sit down and talk ahead of time about how they're going to handle the healing load on the raid's punching bag(s).<br><br>Like Reclamation said it was a looooooong fight but a good one.  As long as one person or group is able to keep the golem's attention, the rest of the raid shouldn't have any problems nuking/beating it down.<br><br><br>--Serving Tunare for 59.4 Seasons on Povar<br>--(You will not evade me Level 60!) <p><p><img src="http://www.users.qwest.net/~copperhawk/Rangersig.gif"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 12:56:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enraged Golem</span><hr size=1>  According to the info i have, the broken golem is a random 24 hour spawn, every 24 hours there is a chance he will spawn, if he has not spawned at the 72 hour mark he will spawn then.<br> 18 to 24 people should be able to do it, but a high end tank is good to have, but like Fallen and Kohpry shows it can be done differently if needed, just improvise <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> Good luck getting the guy down, I still need Phinny *shudders* and I am just waiting for a fear raid so I can get the Broken Golem down.<br><br> <p> <i>Tegellan Fey`Brandhe</i><BR> Evoker of the Fifth Order<Br> The Circle of Eternity - Veeshan<BR> <a href="mailto:tegellan@hotmail.com">tegellan@hotmail.com</a><BR><i>-I am the romancer. The burning passion that consumes the flesh</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uburrowowlx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>burrowowlx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 1:42:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Enraged Golem</span><hr size=1> FWIW: Normal nukes can land on him, but you will get pretty low partial resists often enough to make lures a better choice.<br><br>I don't recall if it can be slowed or not.  I do recall that a fear raid capable of taking out Cazic Thule can handle the golem.  But, that is a totally useless bit of info now, isn't it?<br><br>Burrowowl X<br>Mith Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-s