normal spells might land once in awhile but lures are a better choice.  I don't remember if we slowed him or not.<br><br>3.  He's under a belltower.  It's maybe 15-30 seconds run from Woe.  You don't have to clear the WHOLE plane but a good chunk of it.  He is static.<br><br>4.  We did it with EIGHT people.  The fight lasted over 20 minutes.  Everyone, with the exception of me and I think maybe one other person, was level 60.  Groups went something like this:<br><br>g1:<br>Warrior<br>Cleric<br>Bard<br>Monk<br>Rogue<br>Shaman<br><br>g2:<br>Wizard (me, duh) <br>Enchanter (I think the enchanter was the only other person that wasn't 60.)<br><br>When we did it, the zone was pretty much cleared, however it was starting to repop.  During the 20 minute fight, me and the enchanter were responsible for mezzing/snaring/rooting/kiting no less than five adds for the duration of the fight.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufallendeitydecandidus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FallenDeity Decandidus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 11:20:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enraged Golem</span><hr size=1> -shakes his head-<br> <p>-Fallen/Rec- 58th Evoker < Aquilo Phoenix > <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upyromous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyromous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 12:15:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks</span><hr size=1>   I think I have enough info to get my guild to go after him now.  The bell towers are the things straight out from zone in before gorgons/fingers, right?  I've never really pulled in fear, except for some CR on my twink monk sometimes, so I'm not too sure where everything is.<br><br>Thanks,<br>Pyromous<br><br>btw, sorry I had that posted on general board.  The epic board's existence slipped my mind. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showMessage?topicID=1627.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showMessage?topicID=1628.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1626.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=1626.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.threadControl?topicID=1626.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1626.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1626.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of repli